The presidential candidate of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), Atiku Abubakar, has revealed that the United States government is in support of his candidature.  In an interview with the Voice of America (VOA) monitored Thursday night, Atiku said Nigerians were misinformed that he couldn’t go to the US. He responded ‘yes’ to a question on whether US government officials endorsed him during his conversations with them. When asked whether he was convinced and confident that the American government was in support of his ambition, Atiku said, “There is no doubt because the United States is ready to support any country that is practicing democracy.” He said he was invited to America by many organizations in the US. US government in support of my candidature - Atiku Atiku arrives Washington, meets US officials today How Atiku emerged as Buhari’s main challenger